# Usage

Citations are inline elements styled with semantic accent colors. The key tokens to customize are:

- `--citation-style` to choose the CSL style (applies to citations and references)
- `--citation-color` and `--citation-color-dark` for light/dark emphasis

Any CSL style from https://github.com/citation-style-language/styles is supported, with common aliases (e.g., `apa`, `ama`).

# Tokens

| Token                   | Description                                  | Default Value              |
| ----------------------- | -------------------------------------------- | -------------------------- |
| `--citation-style`      | Citation style name (CSL identifier)         | `apa`                      |
| `--citation-color`      | Citation text color                          | `var(--color-accent)`      |
| `--citation-color-dark` | Citation text color in dark mode             | `var(--color-accent-dark)` |

# Examples

## Default Citations

```css
:root {
  /* No design token overrides */
}
```

::: style

```html raw
<p>
  Recent work <stencila-citation target="smith-2024" citation-mode="Parenthetical"><span slot="content">(Smith et al., 2024)</span></stencila-citation>
  shows improved outcomes across cohorts.
</p>
```

:::

## Numeric Citations

```css
:root {
  --citation-style: vancouver;
  --citation-color: var(--color-blue-600);
}
```

::: style --citation-style: vancouver; --citation-color: var(--color-blue-600);

```html raw
<p>
  See prior studies <stencila-citation-group><span slot="content">[1, 2, 5]</span></stencila-citation-group>
  for comparative baselines.
</p>
```

:::
